<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef734bc4-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idef734bc5-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Executive Order 13790, referred to in subsec. (b)(2), is Ex. Ord. No. 13790, § 6, <date date="2017-04-25">Apr. 25, 2017</date>, 82 F.R. 20239, which is not classified to the Code.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idef734bc6-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="definitions" id="idef734bc7-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Definition of “Secretary”</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">“Secretary” means the Secretary of Agriculture, see <ref href="/us/pl/115/334/s2">section 2 of Pub. L. 115–334</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s9001">section 9001 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
